description.plain:
Michael Ray Nguyen-Stevenson (born November 19, 1989), known by his stage name Tyga (an acronym for Thank You God Always), is an American rapper.

He is currently signed to his own record label, Last Kings Records, where he is the CEO.

He first received recognition with his debut single “Coconut Juice”, featuring his cousin Travie McCoy. After releasing his debut album No Introduction, he signed to Cash Money/Young Money and released his major long-awaited label debut Careless World: Rise of the Last King on February 21, 2012. The album included the chart-topping singles “Rack City”, “Faded”, “Far Away” and “Make It Nasty”. He released his third studio album on April 9, 2013 entitled Hotel California. The album contained singles such as Show You and Switch Lanes. which was successful, despite mixed critical response. After being quitting YMCMB on June 23, 2015, he released his 4th album, The Gold Album: 18th Dynasty which was both a critical and commercial failure.

songs.title: Taste

description.plain:
“Taste”, a trap-influenced, upbeat rap song featuring Migos’ member Offset was published on May 16, 2018. The track marks T-Raww and Offset’s first ever collaboration.

Tyga explained how the song came about:

“I sent it to [Offset] and he FaceTimed me and told me the song was crazy and he wanted to hop on it.”

Taste is probably referring to oral sex.

A music video was released on the same day, depicting Tyga and Offset surrounded by girls dancing to the song at a house party by the pool and on a roller rink. Cameo appearances by A.E., Wiz Khalifa, Ronny J, Joyner Lucas, 2 Chainz and comedian King Bach are featured throughout the video.

songs.title: Rack City

description.plain:
Rack City is a nickname for Las Vegas, the city of racks ($$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$).

 The song originally appeared on Tyga’s mixtape, Well Done 2, in 2010. On November 19, 2010, Rap-Up announced that Rack City would be released to the iTunes Store in the United States as the second single from Careless World: Rise Of The Last King on December 2, 2011.

songs.title: Stimulated

description.plain:
With “Stimulated” Tyga makes an apparent response to the heavy criticism he’s received from his relationship with TV personality Kylie Jenner.

However reportedly, numerous entertainment portals have stated that the Kardashian Klan has not taken Tyga’s explicit discussion about his sex life with Kylie too kindly.
